Adapted components and product references
-----------------------------------------

The following projects have informed Mémoire Studio's interaction patterns and
runtime ideas. Where code or assets were directly adapted, the original
license terms continue to apply to the adapted portions.

- Hermes WebUI (MIT): https://github.com/nesquena/hermes-webui
  Mémoire Studio adapts the transcript-first, calm-console interaction pattern
  and the three-pane workbench organization from the public Hermes WebUI
  project.

- Hermes Agent (MIT): https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent
  Mémoire Studio adapts runtime ideas around agent sessions, normalized
  events, approval-oriented supervision, and local execution boundaries from
  the public Hermes Agent project.

- Warp UI framework (MIT pieces only): https://github.com/warpdotdev/Warp
  Mémoire Studio may reference or adapt MIT-licensed Warp UI framework ideas
  from warpui_core and warpui. Warp's AGPL-licensed application/client code is
  not copied.

- t3code (MIT): https://github.com/pingdotgg/t3code
  Mémoire Studio's harness contracts and event-sourcing patterns are inspired
  by t3code's ProviderRuntime architecture. Pattern-level inspiration only —
  no source is directly copied. The engine implementation lives in the
  Mémoire engine repository.

Product references (no source adapted)
--------------------------------------

- Warp terminal block behavior is used as a product reference for command
  blocks.
- Antigravity Manager view is referenced for the multi-workspace orchestration
  pattern.
- Claude Code, Codex, and OpenCode are referenced as harness targets and for
  comparable feature surfaces (checkpoint/rewind, hooks, walkthrough, etc.).

